STELE — tiny trained language model on the full system (simulation)
====================================================================
model    : order-1 Markov (bigram), MLE-trained on corpus 'fpga works'
           embedded in the quantised SSM pipeline (one-hot embedding,
           ternary bigram LM head; both Mamba layers execute fully,
           W_out=0 so the residual stream carries the token through)
bigram   : ' '->'w' 'a'->' ' 'f'->'p' 'g'->'a' 'k'->'s' 'o'->'r' 'p'->'g' 'r'->'k' 's'->'f' 'w'->'o'

boot     : cfg_mode=1, streamed 64 CSR bytes over uio:
           00 06 00 08 00 01 00 40 00 02 00 80 00 10 00 04
           00 04 00 80 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 04 00 00 00 05
           00 14 00 01 00 00 00 01 25 80 0a 00 10 00 10 80
           15 00 15 80 1d 80 4b 00 53 00 08 00 00 00 00 00
input    : host_drive+in_valid, prompt token 6 ('f') on uio
running  : 20 tokens, autoregressive (embedding -> 2 layers -> LM head argmax per token)...

